Gender Workforce Profile 

As of 30 March 2017 Knowsley Council’s workforce headcount was 2,934 staff.  The majority of the Council’s workforce at this date was female 
(72%); and the majority of these female employees work part-time 42%, with 15% on a casual contract.  92% of the part-time workforce at this 
date was female, meaning that any policy that affects more part-time staff than full-time staff will have a disproportionate impact on women.  

 

