Median full-time gender pay gap 

Out of the 1,599 staff who work full-time for Knowsley Council, 932 are female and 667 male.  The average median hourly rate for all full-time 
staff is £15.02.  The average median hourly rate for male full-time staff is £14.59 and for female staff it is £15.02, meaning that there is a full-
time median gender pay gap of -3%, which is interpreted as no pay gap at all. 

Median part-time gender pay gap 

Out of the 1,021 staff who work part time for Knowsley Council, the vast majority are female (947) with only 74 men working less than full-
time hours.  The average median hourly rate for all part-time staff is £8.90. The median average hourly rate for male part-time staff is £8.63 
and female staff is £8.90 meaning that there is a part-time the gender pay gap of -3.1%, which once again is interpreted as no pay gap at all. 
 
 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

Mean Gender Pay Gap  

The mean gender pay gap is the difference between the mean hourly rate of pay of male full-pay relevant employees and that of female full-
pay relevant employees. The average mean hourly rate across the council is £14.20, the mean hourly rate for females is £13.47 and the mean 
hourly rate for men is £16.05. This equates to a mean pay gap of 16.07%. 

 

 

 

